      • getChexSystemsScore

        public int getChexSystemsScore()
        getChexSystemsScore returns the customer's ChexSystems score. This score is what banks use to determine whether or not a customer is eligible to open a checking account or not. The value ranges from 100 on the low side to 899, just like a credit score. the Customer's chex score is randomly generated for both randomized and customized Customers.
        Returns:
        returns the customer's ChexScore

      • getCreditScore
